claim.claim-text:
14. A communication system for a vehicle, the communication system comprising:
a microphone array comprising a plurality of microphone elements mounted within the vehicle for receiving an acoustic signal and converting the acoustic signal to an electrical signal;
an antenna that is mounted proximate to the microphone array, the antenna communicating a radio frequency signal to a wireless device; and
a controller located remotely from the microphone and antenna and having a first input that is electrically coupled to at least one microphone element in the microphone array and a second input that is electrically coupled to the antenna, the controller processing the electrical signal and transmitting the processed electrical signal to the antenna,
said communication system configured to provide balanced communications, wherein the first input that is electrically coupled to the at least one microphone in the microphone array further comprises:
a first conductor that transmits a non-inverted polarity microphone output signal;
a second conductor that transmits an inverted polarity microphone output signal;
a third conductor that provides a reference point relative to the non-inverted and inverted polarity microphone output signals from the first and second conductors; and
a differential amplifier for converting the non-inverted and inverted polarity microphone output signals from the first and second conductors to a single ended signal.
